“We are training those clan militias, who will be registered as police officers to protect their people,” Galmudug state President Ahmed Abdi Kariye, popularly known as Qor-Qor, told the BBC Somali Service Kariye is a close ally of the federal government and was elected in a disputed regional poll in early February. Since then, he has managed to reconcile with the opposition and has nominated an all-inclusive cabinet, which has enabled him to focus on development and security. --Bbc--